1 WHEREAS, Nellie Tayloe Ross became the first lady of Wyoming
2 in 1922 after her husband, William B. Ross, was elected
3 governor; and
4
5 WHEREAS, Nellie Tayloe Ross was relied upon by her husband,
6 who consulted her daily on political life; and
7
8 WHEREAS, Nellie Tayloe Ross was asked to run for governor by
9 the state party chairman after William B. Ross died a month
10 before the election; and
11
12 WHEREAS, Nellie Tayloe Ross, who had political ambitions, was
13 advised not to run for the office of governor by friends and
14 family but nonetheless accepted her party's nomination on
15 October 14, 1924; and
16
17 WHEREAS, Nellie Tayloe Ross won the gubernatorial election on
18 November 4, 1924, by a margin of approximately ten percent
19 (10%); and
20
21 WHEREAS, Nellie Tayloe Ross assumed office as the first woman
22 governor in the United States on January 5, 1925, tackling
