2 ranch failures and bank failures; and
3
4 WHEREAS, Nellie Tayloe Ross served as governor for one (1)
5 term, but her remarkable political career did not end once
6 she left the governor's office; and
7
8 WHEREAS, Nellie Tayloe Ross once again made history in May
9 1933 when she became the first woman to hold the position of
10 director of the United States mint; and
11
12 WHEREAS, Nellie Tayloe Ross served as director of the United
13 States mint through the Great Depression, World War II and
14 the Korean War and is the longest-serving United States mint
15 director in history; and
16
17 WHEREAS, Nellie Tayloe Ross retired from the United States
18 mint in April 1953 and lived a prosperous life until her death
19 at age one hundred one (101) on December 20, 1977; and
20
21 WHEREAS, Nellie Tayloe Ross remains the only woman to have
22 served as governor of Wyoming and one (1) of seven (7) women
23 to serve as director of the United States mint; and
